* Define multiple DataSource beans
* Use @Primary to mark default datasource
* Use @EnableJpaRepositories with different base packages for each DB
Spring Boot supports multiple databases by manually configuring each datasource.
We create two DataSource beans, two EntityManagerFactory beans, and two TransactionManager beans.
Then, using @EnableJpaRepositories, we map each repository package to the correct database.
Primary beans are marked with @Primary.
